More from FactSet »










Description




Oroplata Resources, Inc. is an exploration mining company engaged in exploration and development of Lithium projects. The Company holds mineral rights in the Dominican Republic and in the Western Nevada Basin of Nye County in the state of Nevada. The Company, through its subsidiary, Oroplata Exploraciones E Ingenieria, Orexi, S.R.L (Oroplata Exploraciones), holds the mineral rights to a claim located in the Dominican Republic, called Mogollon Gold Claim. Lithortech Resources incorporated is a Company's subsidiary. The Mogollon gold concession is located in the province of San Juan, in the Dominican Republic. As of September 30, 2016, the Company's Western Nevada Basin (WNB) Property was located in east central Nye County, Nevada, approximately 93 miles northeast of the county seat of Tonopah, Nevada; 56 miles southwest of the town of Ely, Nevada, and 120 miles northeast of the village of Silver Peak. As of September 30, 2016, the Company had not generated any revenues.


